snippet.textDisplay: I'm a point blank student and I am Bangladeshi. However, even though we had an amazing first episode, I cannot get this out of my head and I ended up using my 1 on 1 session with my lecturer just talking about how awesome this is. Bear in mind, the particular lecturer is from London, the apparent trend setter in music but after hearing this, he is firmly of the opinion that Coke Studio Season 14 is the most interesting thing happening in music in the world at the moment. I am of the same opinion. Massive respect to all involved!!!

snippet.textDisplay: Love the fact pak is bring back its own unique style although we are cultural but this so called “modern era” has always been of pak since 60s till 90s example nazia hasan from Pakistan she was known the south Asians pop queen known from pak till Latin America. Example ko ko korina so ahead of its time. Pakistan’s bands vital signs junoon strong etc. Although we had punjabi lollywood we still had our own touch our own Urdu/farsi then neighbouring countries who known as chappa factory ahem..... stole our songs still do till day infact. But we started losing our touch to next door shittywood who actually uses our unique PAKISTAN culture be it language or even attire. Plz if were gonna be traditional be our own traditional and our own modern too I mean just look at the creativity of the art design set etc. 🥰🇵🇰✌️
